<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Mutton" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Mutton,</orth> 1) a sheep: <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.1.101" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. I, 1, 101</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.1.101" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. I, 1, 101</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mv 1.3.168" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 3, 168</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.57" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 2, 57</bibl>.<lb />2) the flesh of sheep dressed for food: <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.304" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 1, 304</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.1.163" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 1, 163</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 1.3.130" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 3, 130</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.376" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 4, 376</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.1.28" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 28</bibl>.
<lb />2) woman's flesh: <cit><quote>the duke would eat m. on Fridays,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.192" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 2, 192</bibl></cit>; cf. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.376" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 4, 376</bibl>. See <emph>Laced mutton.</emph>
